-- France denies planning to sell part of EDF stake
-- By Jean-Baptiste Vey
-- Tue May 27, 2014 08:44AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, May 27 (Reuters) - The French state has no plans to sell a 15 percent stake in EDF <EDF.PA>, a finance ministry official told Reuters on Tuesday, denying a union report that the government was preparing to reduce its 84 percent holding in the power group.

"We categorically deny" that the government is planning to sell the stake, the official said.